WHAT IS AN INTERRUPT?

- INT xx  ;interrupt range from 00h to FFh
- an INT is just like a FAR CALL but it saves also the flag register.

BOIS INT 10H PROGRAMMING used for screen IO
- monitor screen mode (graphics and text modes)
  - text mode
    the pixels are cobioned into groups 8 by 8 pixel per letter
    the screen has 80 column and 25 rows number from (0, 0) at the
    top left corner and (0, 79) at the top right corner and from
    (24, 0) at the bottom left corner and (24, 79) at the bottom right corner
  
  - Clearing the screen INT 10H with functino 06H
    INT 10H is used
    AH = 06H is a scroll up function
    AL = 0 for clear otherwise will be number of lines to scroll
    BH = is back ground color see bios color attributes(16 colors)
    CX = 0000 CH upper row number , CL left column number
    DX = 184Fh DH lower row number, DL right column number

  - Setting the curser to a specific postion
    INT 10h is used
    AH = 02h set curser function
    BH = page number
    DH row number
    DL column number

  - Get the cursor position
    INT 10h is used
    AH = 03h function number
    BH = 00 page number
    the row will be in DH and the column in DL

  - read to know about pixel programming.
 
